{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012TJGHNuEggvFHqHE7nUydU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All requirements are met. Here's a summary of what was found and fixed:\n\n**Problems found:**\n1. `/app` vhost — `app-user` had empty configure permission (`\"\"`) but needed `\".*\"` (blocking queue declaration)\n2. `/app` vhost — `ops-user` had full permissions there (wrong vhost entirely)\n3. `/ops` vhost — `ops-user` had zero permissions (couldn't access the vhost at all)\n4. A secondary issue: `app-queue` in `/app` had been pre-created with `x-queue-mode=lazy`, causing an argument mismatch when `app-client` tried to re-declare it — deleted the queue so the client could create it correctly\n\n**Actions taken (all via `rabbitmqctl`):**\n- `set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — restored full configure/write/read for app-user on /app\n- `clear_permissions -p /app ops-user` — removed ops-user's cross-vhost access to /app\n- `set_permissions -p /ops ops-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` — granted ops-user full permissions on /ops\n- `delete_queue app-queue -p /app` — cleared the mismatched pre-existing queue\n\n**End state:**\n- `app-user`: `.*`/`.*`/`.*` on `/app` only\n- `ops-user`: `.*`/`.*`/`.*` on `/ops` only\n- `app-client` and `ops-client`: both `1/1 Running`\n- All 3 RabbitMQ nodes: running healthy"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1048,"cache_read_input_tokens":35545,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1048},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"52e840dc-2555-475d-bb0c-9c2f9f27aa7f","uuid":"4128ff3c-1373-49c3-b823-bbafb186061b","request_id":"req_011Ccc2Geh2L75zmMt6adJSA"}
